title: Warren Zevon - Rockefeller's, Houston, TX 06-18-1986 (SBD) [FLAC
description:
A high class solo perfomance by Warren Zevon - quite wide spread among bootleg collectors. Nevertheless there's written some nonsense about this recording in the net:
CD1 track 1 is definitely NOT Warren Zevon on different fiddles at the same time, playing Jimi's Purple Haze. It's Purple Haze by the Kronos Quartet probably from a tape as an intro to Warren's performance.
CD2 track 1 is definitely 'Jungle Work' and not 'Strike The Muscle'



Warren Zevon - Solo Performance
Rockefeller's, Houston, Texas
June 18, 1986
Early Show 

Unofficial Soundboard Recording - Excellent Sound Quality

CD1:
01. Purple Haze (Kronos Quartet)
02. Lawyers, Guns and Money
03. Jeannie Needs a Shooter
04. Reconsider Me
05. Roland the Headless Thompson Gunner
06. Johnny Strikes Up the Band
07. The Factory
08. Boom Boom Mancini

CD2
01. Jungle Work
02. Tenderness on the Block
03. Accidentally Like a Martyr
04. Werewolves of London > Mohammed's Radio 
05. Crowd
06. Summertime Blues > Poor Poor Pitiful Me
07. Crowd Outro
